###
### 📚 API TESTS INDEX
### HyggeHub API Testing Suite
###
### This file serves as a quick reference to all available API test files.
### Use rest.nvim in LazyVim to execute these tests.
###
### 📖 HOW TO USE:
### 1. Open any .http file in this directory
### 2. Update the variables section at the top
### 3. Place cursor on any request
### 4. Run :Rest run (or :Rest run [request-name] for named requests)
### 5. View results with :Rest open
###
### 📋 AVAILABLE TEST FILES:
###
### 👤 users.http          - User management endpoints
###    GET    /api/users             - Get user's organizations
###    PATCH  /api/users             - Add shop code to user
###    PUT    /api/users             - Update user birthday
###    DELETE /api/users             - Remove shop code from user
###
### 🏢 orgs.http           - Organization/Shop management endpoints
###    GET    /api/orgs              - Get organization info and customers
###    POST   /api/orgs              - Add new message to shop
###    PUT    /api/orgs              - Update shop code/phone/messages
###    DELETE /api/orgs              - Delete customer or message
###
### 👥 customers.http      - Customer management endpoints
###    POST   /api/customers         - Subscribe customer(s) to shop
###
### 📱 sms-notif.http      - SMS notification endpoints
###    POST   /api/sms-notif         - Send SMS to recipient(s)
###
### 🔗 webhooks.http       - Clerk webhook integration endpoints
###    POST   /api/webhooks/clerk-sync - Handle Clerk events
###
### 🔧 REST.NVIM COMMANDS:
###
### :Rest run                    - Run request under cursor
### :Rest run [request-name]     - Run specific named request
### :Rest last                   - Re-run last request
### :Rest open                   - Open results pane
### :Rest logs                   - View logs
### :Rest env show               - Show current .env file
### :Rest env select             - Select .env file
### :Rest env set [path]         - Set specific .env file
###
### 🔐 AUTHENTICATION:
###
### All endpoints require:
### - x-api-key header (global API key)
###
### Most endpoints also require:
### - x-clerk-user-id header (user context)
### - x-clerk-org-id header (organization context)
###
### 📝 VARIABLE MANAGEMENT:
###
### Each test file has a variables section at the top:
### @baseUrl = http://localhost:3000
### @apiKey = your-api-key-here
### @userId = user_xxxxxxxxxxxxx
###
### Simply update these values once, and all requests will use them.
###
### 💡 TIPS:
###
### - Use ### to separate requests
### - Name requests with ### [name] for easy access
### - Use {{variable}} syntax for variable substitution
### - Add # @lang=lua above script blocks for Lua scripting
### - Check response in split pane after running requests
### - Use :Rest last to quickly re-run the previous request
###
### 🚀 QUICK START:
###
### 1. Update API key and base URL in each test file
### 2. Get your Clerk user ID and org ID from your dev console
### 3. Open users.http and try running the first request
### 4. Check the results pane to see the response
###
### Happy testing! 🎉
###
